column14: ON FURTHER REVIEW, TAG 33.00 ONLY HAS ONE GOOD BIN, AND APPEARS TO UNDERESTIMATE VELOCITIES OBSERVED IN EDGE. THERE IS NOT AS SIGNIFICANT OF CHANGE IN DEPTH BETWEEN TAGS 31.00 TO 33.00 AS FIRST ASSUMED BY THE DROP TO 1 BIN. REVISED TO USING THE MMT WITH TAG 33.00 REMOVED. NO OTHER CHANGES MADE.   Started moving bed test, losing bins not because of depth. Changed batteries as voltage was low, no improvement. Switched to SXS. Calling it M2 to keep data attempted in moving boat. Most panels looked good, a few had scattered invalid ensembles. Dropped to 0-1 good bins after tag 31.00, too shallow from there to far edge, causing large right edge (total Q 23.6). Left in poor quality data at tag 33.00 because it better represents the edge DEPTH than the tag 31.00 data. SD warnings on tag 3.00 due to flow changes, not changes in boat direction.  @ Uncertainty: ISO method, 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ Mid-section

column14: Aborted 4th transect as it started too close to shore. Transects 3-5 slightly downstream of rest to try to avoid a rock's eddy, but got into <2 bins issues. Did 2 extra transects to address this, and all 6 complete transects ended up agreeing, so leaving them in. This is first mmt since extreme high water event this summer and is on the lower end of the curve. Difference is likely is due to control change due to high water event (NOTE: EHSN CURVE WAS INCORRECT. AFTER LOADING IN AQ, MMT PLOTS <5%). GPS track was wonky, at times not changing at all during the transect. Checked all cables were properly attached, with no change seen. No reset applied on logger: surging around DWL and found within 0.003 initially. ADCP by Moving Boat
